From: NextOS Elite <noreply@nextos.local>
Subject: [PATCH] include/elf.h: delegate to system when HOSTCC

u-boot/include/elf.h tem defs ELF legacy mas falta Elf64_Rela (moderno).
Quando host-tools precisam disso, falha com 'Elf64_Rela undeclared'.

Fix: quando USE_HOSTCC, pula direto pro system <elf.h> via include_next
ANTES do guard #define _ELF_H (senão system elf.h vê guard já definido
e skippa tudo — o bug que causava Elf64_Rela unknown).

---
 include/elf.h | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/elf.h b/include/elf.h
--- a/include/elf.h
+++ b/include/elf.h
@@ -9,6 +9,12 @@
  * formerly known as "elf_abi.h".
  */
 
+#ifdef USE_HOSTCC
+/* Host tools: usa elf.h do sistema (tem Elf64_Rela etc). include_next
+ * ANTES do guard _ELF_H senão system header é skippado. */
+#include_next <elf.h>
+#else /* !USE_HOSTCC */
+
 #ifndef _ELF_H
 #define _ELF_H
 
@@ -541,4 +547,6 @@
 
 int valid_elf_image(unsigned long addr);
 
+#endif /* !USE_HOSTCC */
+
 #endif /* _ELF_H */
